sections.text:
53-103.50.Channel pricing, defined.

Channel pricing means a pricing strategy that differentiates the price charged for a product based upon the type of license held by the retailer and the primary use of the premises on which the retailer operates.

SourceLaws 2023, LB376, ยง 3.
